Task Title: Build a Simple “To-Do List” App (Local State Only)
Goal:

Create a small Flutter app that allows the user to add, view, and delete tasks using basic state management (setState or Provider).

 Requirements
1. UI Requirements

Home screen containing:

An AppBar titled “To-Do List”

A TextField + an “Add” button to enter new task

A scrollable list of tasks

Each task must be displayed in a ListTile with:

Task name

A delete icon (Icons.delete) to remove the task

2. Functional Requirements

User can add a task

User can delete a task

Display a Snackbar on add or delete

All state stored locally in memory (no database needed)

3. Technical Requirements

Use Flutter 3+

State management options allowed:

setState

Or Provider (optional)

Clean, readable code

Use a Widget class for the list


////////////////////////// no need ask information  ////////////////////////////

Bonus (Optional – if time allows)

Add a “mark as completed” checkbox

Persist tasks using SharedPreferences

⏱️ Time Estimate

UI layout: 20 minutes

Adding/deleting logic: 20 minutes

Cleanup + testing: 20 minutes
Total: 1 hour
